The paper focuses on a large-scale dataset for UAV perception in aggressive flight, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The dataset is collected for evaluation of agile perception, which can be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of photorealistic rendering, which can be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
